Cleaning of Data¶

In [ ]:
df.isnull().sum()
Out[ ]:
mean_radius        0
mean_texture       0

mean_area          0
mean_smoothness    0
diagnosis          0

No extra cleaning is required because the data has no NaN values¶

Now we have Cancer not found as 0 and Cancer found as 1 so we Convert the Categorical features to dummy numerical variables so that the model can consider it accordingly¶

In [ ]:
df["diagnosis"].replace("NF",0,inplace = True)
df["diagnosis"].replace("F",1,inplace = True)

Normalisation and Splitting¶

The data is split and is normalised accordingly¶

In [ ]:
y = df.diagnosis.values
x = df.drop("diagnosis",axis=1)
x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.3)
In [ ]:
scaler = MinMaxScaler()
cols = x_train.columns
temp = scaler.fit_transform(x_train)
x_train = pd.DataFrame(temp,columns=cols)

cols = x_test.columns
temp = scaler.fit_transform(x_test)
x_test = pd.DataFrame(temp,columns=cols)

In [ ]:
x = np.column_stack((x_train)) 
y = y_train
x_train = sm.add_constant(x_train)

Now we Proceed to build the model and predict the values¶

In [ ]:
logregmodel = logreg()
logregmodel.fit(x_train,y_train)
predictions = logregmodel.predict(x_test)

Classification Report¶

In [ ]:
print(classification_report(y_test,predictions))

              precision    recall  f1-score   support

In [ ]:
cfm = confusion_matrix(y_test, predictions)

print('True Negative:', cfm[0][0])
print('False Positive:', cfm[0][1])
print('False Negative:', cfm[1][0])
print('True Positive:', cfm[1][1])
print('Correct Predictions', round((cfm[0][0] + cfm[1][1]) / len(predictions) * 100, 1), '%')
